ublisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Mi-kyung|last=Sun|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=109&aid=0004168332|title='\ubd80\ubd80\uc758 \uc138\uacc4' \uae40\ud76c\uc560X\ubc15\ud574\uc900, \uc544\uc2ac\ud558\uace0 \uce58\uba85\uc801\uc778 \uc228\uba4e 2\ucc28 \ud3ec\uc2a4\ud130 \uacf5\uac1c[Oh!\uc388 \ucef7]|date=February 19, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020|website=Osen|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref> It has currently the second-highest viewership ratings as a JTBC drama and is currently the third [[Korean drama#List%20of%20highest-rated%20Korean%20dramas%20in%20cable%20television|highest rated drama in Korean cable television history]].\n\n==Synopsis==\nJi Sun-woo, a medical doctor who seemingly lives a perfect life, starts to seek revenge on her husband who is having an affair.\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Kim Hee-ae]] as Ji Sun-woo\n* [[Park Hae-joon]] as Lee Tae-oh\n* [[Han So-hee]] as Yeo Da-kyung<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/han-so-hee-so-star-in-the-world-of-the-married-134322.html|date=October 7, 2019|work=[[HanCinema]]|title=Han So-hee To Star in \"The World of the Married\"|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Park Sun-young (actress)|Park Sun-young]] as Go Ye-rim\n* Kim Young-min as Son Je-hyuk\n* Chae Gook-hee as Seol Myung-sook\n* [[Lee Geung-young]] as Yeo Byung-gyu\n* Kim Sun-kyung as Eom Hyo-jung\n* Jeon Jin-seo as Lee Joon-yeong\n\n==Supporting==\n* Park Choong-sun as Ma Kang-seok\n* Jung Jae-sung as Gong Ji-cheol\n* Lee Moo-saeng as Kim Yoon-gi<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/lee-moo-saeng-to-star-in-the-world-of-the-married-136407.html|date=December 4, 2019|work=[[HanCinema]]|title=Lee Moo-saeng to Star in \"The World of the Married\"|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* Kim Jong-tae as Ha Dong-sik\n* Seo Yi-sook as Chairman Choi's wife\n* Lee Hak-joo as Park In-gyu\n* Shim Eun-woo as Min Hyun-seo\n\n==Original soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = The World of the Married 